source("helperFunctions.R")

integrated_seurat <- readRDS("data/integrated_seurat.rds")

integrated_seurat <- subset(integrated_seurat, subset = Sample_Tag != "NA")
#colSums(is.na(integrated_seurat@meta.data))

summary(integrated_seurat@meta.data$percent.mt)

   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
  0.000   1.041   1.454   1.685   2.078   4.995 
integrated_seurat@meta.data$factor.mt <- cut(integrated_seurat@meta.data$percent.mt,
                                             breaks = c(-Inf, 1.041, 1.454, 2.078, Inf),
                                             labels = c("Low", "Medium", "Medium high", "High"))

DimPlot(integrated_seurat, group.by = "factor.mt") +
  labs(title = "UMAP showing all samples \n grouped by the mitochondrial expression")


DimPlot(integrated_seurat,
        group.by = "factor.mt",
        split.by = "Sample_Tag") +
  labs(title = "UMAP of all samples grouped by \n their sample tags and \n splitted by mitochondrial expression")


# Extract identity and cell cylce phases from seurat object to determine the number of cells with mitochondiral expression.
n_cells_mt <- FetchData(integrated_seurat,
                           vars = c("ident", "factor.mt")) %>%
              dplyr::count(ident, factor.mt) %>%
              tidyr::spread(ident, n)

View(n_cells_mt)

datatable(n_cells_mt,
          caption = "The table shows the number of cells with mitochondrial expression.")

subset_pilots <- subset(integrated_seurat, seq_folder == "1820" | seq_folder == "1822")
subset_1820 <- subset(integrated_seurat, seq_folder == "1820")
subset_70_71 <- subset(integrated_seurat, seq_folder == "7270" | seq_folder == "7271")
subset_7272 <- subset(integrated_seurat, seq_folder == "7272")
subset_7273 <- subset(integrated_seurat, seq_folder == "7273")
subset_control <- subset(integrated_seurat, Sample_Tag == "Control")
subset_alpelisib <- subset(integrated_seurat, Sample_Tag == "Alpelisib")
subset_copanlisib <- subset(integrated_seurat, Sample_Tag == "Copanlisib")

DimPlot(subset_1820, 
        split.by = "Sample_Tag",
        group.by = "factor.mt") +
  labs(title = "UMAP 1820 sample tags combined \n with mitochondrial expression",
       caption = "Sample 1820 grouped by the mitochondrial expression and \n splitted by the different sample tags.") +
  theme(plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

DimPlot(subset_1820,
        group.by = "Sample_Tag") +
  labs(title = "UMAP visualisation of \n all sample tags from sample 1820.")
